SIMPLE: safflower
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Safflower
<hw>Saf"flow`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>safleur</ets>, <ets>saflor</ets>, for <ets>safran</ets>, influenced
by <ets>fleur</ets> flower. See <er>Saffron</er>, and
<er>Flower</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An annual
composite plant (<spn>Carthamus tinctorius</spn>), the flowers of which
are used as a dyestuff and in making rouge; bastard, or false,
saffron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The dried flowers of the <spn>Carthamus
tinctorius</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A dyestuff from these flowers. See <er>Safranin</er>
<sd>(b)</sd>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Oil of safflower</b></col>, <cd>a purgative oil expressed
from the seeds of the safflower.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saffron</ent>⟦br⟧
